Class BitSpliterator.Dead

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.shouldis.bitset.BitSpliterator
      • com.shouldis.bitset.BitSpliterator.Dead
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Spliterator<java.lang.Integer>, java.util.Spliterator.OfInt, java.util.Spliterator.OfPrimitive<java.lang.Integer,​java.util.function.IntConsumer,​java.util.Spliterator.OfInt>
    Enclosing class:
    BitSpliterator
    public static final class BitSpliterator.Dead
extends BitSpliterator
    Implementation of BitSpliterator used to stream the indices of dead bits within a BitSet, splitting at appropriate indices to manipulate a BitSet in parallel. Words are cached as they are encountered, so any modifications after iteration begins may not be included.

      • next

        private int next​(int index)
        Calculates the index of the next dead bit after the specified index, including that index. All bits indices until BitSpliterator.end will be checked. If no live bits are found, BitSpliterator.end is returned.
        Parameters:
        index - (inclusive) the first index to check.
        Returns:
        the index of the next dead bit, or BitSpliterator.end if none were found.
